%I A394759 #6 Apr 07 2026 22:20:09
%S A394759 1,2,2,6,6,14,6,22,22,48,18,80,80
%N A394759 Number of graceful labelings of the balanced bistar tree on n vertices.
%C A394759 Let B(a,b) be the tree obtained by joining the centers of two stars with a and b leaves.
%C A394759 For n >= 2, define a = ceil((n-2)/2), b = floor((n-2)/2). Then a(n) is the number of graceful labelings of B(a,b).
%C A394759 A graceful labeling assigns labels 0,1,...,n-1 to the vertices so that all edge differences are distinct.
%D A394759 Douglas B. West, Introduction to Graph Theory, Pearson Education Pte. Ltd, 2002, page 81.
%H A394759 Igor Blokhin, <a href="https://github.com/IgorBlokhin/Graph-Theory">Graceful Prüfer Codes</a> (Python repository).
%e A394759 For n=4 there are 2 such labelings: 1--2--0--3 and 0--3--1--2, so a(4)=2.
%Y A394759 Cf. A033472.
%K A394759 nonn,hard,more,new
%O A394759 2,2
